cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper deals with remote photo-plethysmography (rPPG) using a camera to estimate heart rate and heart rate variability. This involves computer vision techniques for motion suppression and filtering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with human-computer interaction (HCI) and physiological measurements, which suggests cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as the second likely category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for filtering and motion suppression, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the third and fourth likely categories. Finally, the paper involves physiological measurements and signal processing, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the fifth likely category.
